HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 319
By Reeves
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Mark Burns on
winning his fifth martial arts world title.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing a
gentleman who has attained the very acme of martial arts competition while serving a higher
purpose in his community; and
WHEREAS, Mark Burns had won four ATA Martial Arts world titles, the last in 2010,
before retiring from competition; and
WHEREAS, in 2024, which marked ATA's fifty-fifth anniversary, Mr. Burns returned to
competitive martial arts and won his fifth ATA world title in creative forms, an incredible
accomplishment considering that he had undergone hip replacements in the interim; and
WHEREAS, in the previous year, Mark Burns and his wife, Ariana, had taken a leap of
faith and opened their own martial arts school, Honor Martial Arts, so named to honor God; and
WHEREAS, through Mr. Burns's deft guidance, Honor Martial Arts seeks to develop
leaders, strengthen families, and build a community grounded in faith, character, and
perseverance, in addition to teaching martial arts; and
WHEREAS, Honor Martial Arts focuses on faith-based values, personal growth, and
serving others and utilizes martial arts as a tool to build confidence, discipline, and resilience
that extends far beyond competition and self-defense; and
WHEREAS, Mark Burns discovered his enduring passion for martial arts in 1989, when
at the age of nine, he began practicing taekwondo at a school located in the basement of a
Chinese restaurant in Elkhart, Indiana; and
WHEREAS, he opened his first martial arts school in 2000 in Kalamazoo, Michigan; after
nearly a decade there, he took a break to refocus, before eventually joining Karate Atlanta,
