where he spent the next ten years developing schools, training students, and growing as an
instructor and leader; and
WHEREAS, in December 2016, Mr. Burns was experiencing a difficult time in his life and
felt truly lost; from these depths of despair, he found the promise and solace of Christianity and
accepted Jesus as his Lord and Savior; and
WHEREAS, as he began to find true purpose in his life through his relationship with
God, Mark Burns was blessed to meet his future wife; battling through the COVID pandemic
together, Mark and Ariana were married in September 2020 and welcomed their son Micah into
the world in August 2021; and
WHEREAS, Mark and Ariana Burns and Honor Martial Arts are nurturing our future
leaders by teaching them time-honored values in addition to martial arts; and
WHEREAS, this martial arts world champion is most deserving of our approbation; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Mark Burns on winning his fifth ATA Martial
Arts world title in creative forms, thank him for his ongoing commitment to positively influencing
and directing his students' lives, and extend to him our best wishes for much continued success
and happiness in the future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
